 {"id":"bd-160","title":"Implement migration file generator","description":"# Task: Implement Migration File Generator

## Context
The migration file generator takes schema diffs and DDL statements and writes them to version-controlled migration files that can be executed in order.

## Design Goals
1. **Timestamped versions**: Unique, orderable migration IDs
2. **Up/Down migrations**: Both forward and rollback DDL
3. **Human-readable**: Formatted SQL with comments
4. **Tracking table**: Record which migrations have been applied

## What to Implement

### 1. Migration File Structure
\`\`\`
migrations/
├── 20260127120000_create_heroes_table.rs    # or .sql
├── 20260127120100_add_team_id_to_heroes.rs
└── 20260127120200_create_powers_table.rs
\`\`\`

### 2. Migration Struct
\`\`\`rust
/// A database migration with up/down operations.
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct Migration {
    /// Unique version identifier (timestamp-based)
    pub version: String,
    /// Human-readable description
    pub description: String,
    /// Forward migration SQL statements
    pub up: Vec<String>,
    /// Rollback migration SQL statements
    pub down: Vec<String>,
    /// Timestamp when migration was created
    pub created_at: chrono::DateTime<chrono::Utc>,
}

impl Migration {
    /// Generate version from current timestamp.
    pub fn new_version() -> String {
        chrono::Utc::now().format("%Y%m%d%H%M%S").to_string()
    }

    /// Create from schema diff.
    pub fn from_diff(diff: &SchemaDiff, ddl: &impl DdlGenerator, description: &str) -> Self {
        let version = Self::new_version();
        let up = ddl.generate_all(&diff.ops);
        let down = ddl.generate_rollback(&diff.ops);

        Self {
            version,
            description: description.to_string(),
            up,
            down,
            created_at: chrono::Utc::now(),
        }
    }
}
